  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a circular loop of wire with radius R that carries a current I counterclockwise.\" src=\"/images/ca9622858f944d61f8ef541eac08a6f9.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A wire is formed into a circular loop of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span>. The loop is then attached to a source of constant potential difference <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta V\"><math alttext=\"delta V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>V</mi></math></span></span>, and the resulting current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub 1\"><math alttext=\"I sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> through the loop creates a magnetic field of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 1\"><math alttext=\"B sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> at the center of the loop. The same wire is then used to form a second circular loop of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 R\"><math alttext=\"2 R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></math></span></span>. If this second loop is connected to the same source of constant potential difference <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta V\"><math alttext=\"delta V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>V</mi></math></span></span>, how does the current <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub 2\"><math alttext=\"I sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> in the second loop and the magnetic field <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 2\"><math alttext=\"B sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> at the center of the second loop compare to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub 1\"><math alttext=\"I sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 1\"><math alttext=\"B sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>, respectively?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><colgroup><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1 colwidth:35\"><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:60\"><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:75\"></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row rowsep:1\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\"></th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Current</th><th class=\"entry colname:col3\">Magnetic Field</th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody valign:middle\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">A</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub 2 is less than, I sub 1\"><math alttext=\"I sub 2 is less than, I sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span></td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B sub 2 is less than, B sub 1\"><math alttext=\"B sub 2 is less than, B sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span></td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">B</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"I sub 2 is less than,